name: CloneNotSupportedException
comment:
Thrown to indicate that the clone method in class Object has been called to clone an object, but that the object's class does not implement the Cloneable interface.

Applications that override the clone method can also throw this exception to indicate that an object could not or should not be cloned.

constructors.name: CloneNotSupportedException
constructors.comment: Constructs a CloneNotSupportedException with no detail message.

constructors.name: CloneNotSupportedException
constructors.comment: Constructs a CloneNotSupportedException with the specified detail message.
